成功，尽管世界各国都在以极快的速度安装这项技术。我一一反驳了怀疑论者的论点，但有一个我从未反驳过——太阳能造成了难以控制的浪费。</p><p>现在，汉娜·里奇（Hannah Ritchie），我最喜欢的气候博主之一，已经<a href="https://www.sustainabilitybynumbers.com/p/renewables-waste">完成了有关太阳能废物（还有风能废物）的工作</a>： </p><div class="embedded-post-wrap" data-attrs="{&quot;id&quot;:138994586,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.sustainabilitybynumbers.com/p/renewables-waste&quot;,&quot;publication_id&quot;:1199196,&quot;publication_name&quot;:&quot;Sustainability by numbers&quot;,&quot;publication_logo_url&quot;:&quot;https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0b3f5948-e0e4-4164-975a-d4b800dedf19_1080x1080.png&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;How much waste do solar panels and wind turbines produce?&quot;,&quot;truncated_body_text&quot;:&quot;You might have seen the following image from a recent paper from Heather Mirletz and colleagues, published in Nature Physics. It has been shared a lot in my circles on social media. The authors estimate that solar waste in 2050 will be very small compared to other waste flows.&quot;,&quot;date&quot;:&quot;2023-11-20T07:13:47.929Z&quot;,&quot;like_count&quot;:76,&quot;comment_count&quot;:46,&quot;bylines&quot;:[{&quot;id&quot;:10269516,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;Hannah Ritchie&quot;,&quot;handle&quot;:&quot;hannahritchie&quot;,&quot;previous_name&quot;:null,&quot;photo_url&quot;:&quot;https://bucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/a1c29882-5c6a-4cc3-b75c-33c816385d72_400x400.jpeg&quot;,&quot;bio&quot;:null,&quot;profile_set_up_at&quot;:&quot;2022-11-18T09:25:42.905Z&quot;,&quot;publicationUsers&quot;:[{&quot;id&quot;:1153597,&quot;user_id&quot;:10269516,&quot;publication_id&quot;:1199196,&quot;role&quot;:&quot;admin&quot;,&quot;public&quot;:true,&quot;is_primary&quot;:false,&quot;publication&quot;:{&quot;id&quot;:1199196,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;Sustainability by numbers&quot;,&quot;subdomain&quot;:&quot;hannahri